Cricket South Africa Fires President Mtutuzeli Nyoka, Business Day Reports

-- B y   G o r d o n   B e l l
-- 
2011-02-14T05:41:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-14/cricket-south-africa-fires-president-mtutuzeli-nyoka-business-day-reports.html
Cricket  South Africa  fired its
president, Mtutuzeli Nyoka, after a vote of no confidence,
Business Day reported, citing acting president, AK Khan.  Nyoka had been in a dispute with Cricket South Africa Chief
Executive Officer Gerald Majola since November over bonuses paid
to officials, the Johannesburg-based newspaper said.  Nyoka promised to expose corruption in the running of the
game in the country, Business Day reported.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gordon Bell at 
 gbell16@bloomberg.net  